### Mistake 4: `break` in the wrong place

**What happened:** The `break` (to stop comparing after the **first** differing character) was placed inside the `if edge is new` block. It should fire whenever a difference is found, regardless of whether the edge is new.

**Lesson:** The `break` belongs to the `if words[i][j] != words[i+1][j]` block, not the inner edge-check:
```python
if words[i][j] != words[i+1][j]:
    if words[i+1][j] not in adjLst[words[i][j]]:
        adjLst[words[i][j]].add(words[i+1][j])
        indegree[words[i+1][j]] += 1
    break  # ← always break after the first difference
```

---

### Quick Takeaway

| Category | Mistake | Key Idea |
|----------|---------|----------|
| Graph building | Indegree not guarded against duplicates | Sync indegree with actual edges |
| Edge case | No prefix check | `len(a) > len(b)` + `a.startswith(b)` → `""` |
| Python syntax | Wrong indentation = dead code | Verify loop nesting after adding guards |
| Logic | `break` scoped too narrowly | Break on first diff, not on new edge |
